      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(proxy): apply enhanced NO_PROXY matching to global undici dispatcher (fixes #95998)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95998.\n\nWhen `HTTPS_PROXY` is set, the global EnvHttpProxyAgent routes ALL requests through the proxy — including internal plugin requests that should bypass via `NO_PROXY`. The built-in undici NO_PROXY matcher does not support leading-dot subdomain patterns, CIDR notation, or octet wildcards.\n\nOpenClaw already has `matchesNoProxy()` that handles these — but it was only used by provider helpers, not the global dispatcher.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n1. **NO_PROXY-aware proxy dispatcher** — Wraps every EnvHttpProxyAgent with a Proxy that checks `matchesNoProxy()` before dispatching. Bypassed requests are routed through a direct Agent.\n\n2. **Lifecycle synchronization (P1 fix)** — Promise-style `close()`/`destroy()` now await both the bypass agent AND the proxy dispatcher. `destroy(err)` arguments are forwarded correctly.\n\n3. **no_proxy precedence (P1 fix)** — Empty lowercase `no_proxy` now correctly shadows uppercase `NO_PROXY`, matching undici's EnvHttpProxyAgent semantics.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Unit tests (90/90 passed):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/net/proxy-env.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  55 passed (55)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/net/undici-global-dispatcher.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  35 passed (35)\n```\n\n**no_proxy / NO_PROXY precedence (matching undici):**\n```\n  ✅ empty no_proxy shadows NO_PROXY: false (bypass nothing)\n  ✅ NO_PROXY only (uppercase): true (fallback works)\n  ✅ no_proxy match: true (lowercase wins)\n  ✅ non-matching: false\n```\n\n**CIDR and octet-wildcard (undici v8.5.0 lacks both):**\n```\n  ✅ CIDR 100.64.0.0/10 match\n  ✅ CIDR outside range: no match\n  ✅ Octet-wildcard 100.100.*.* match\n  ✅ Octet-wildcard outside: no match\n  ✅ Leading-dot .myqcloud.com match\n  ✅ Leading-dot subdomain: sub.sub.example.com -> .example.com match\n```\n\n**Live proxy verification (5 scenarios):**\nA local HTTP proxy (127.0.0.1:18999) was started with `HTTPS_PROXY` configured. The global dispatcher was initialized with the NO_PROXY-aware wrapper, then `fetch()` requests were made under different NO_PROXY configurations.\n\n- Without NO_PROXY → routes through proxy\n- NO_PROXY=.myqcloud.com → COS domain bypasses proxy\n- Non-matching domain → routes through proxy\n- CIDR 100.64.0.0/10 → bypasses proxy (undici cannot do this)\n- Octet-wildcard 100.100.*.* → bypasses proxy (undici cannot do this)\n\n## AI Assistance\n\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
